OL,3,CNext government should consider
OL,4,Cbanning phones for under-16s, report
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FBut the committee has said this does
OL,8,Fnot go far enough.
OL,10,FIts report said the next government
OL,11,Fshould consult on raising the age of
OL,12,Fdigital consent from 13 to 16, and
OL,13,Fshould consider a total ban on
OL,14,Fsmartphones for under-16s, as well as
OL,15,Fa full statutory ban on mobile phones
OL,16,Fin schools, pointing to a rise in
OL,17,Fchildren's screen time and phone use
OL,18,Fthat is consistent with a behavioural
OL,19,Faddiction.
