OL,3,CNext government should consider
OL,4,Cbanning phones for under-16s, report
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,F"Our inquiry heard shocking statistics
OL,8,Fon the extent of the damage being done
OL,9,Fto under-18s, particularly those who
OL,10,Fare already extremely vulnerable, such
OL,11,Fas those in care.
OL,13,F"Without urgent action, more children
OL,14,Fwill be put in harm's way. From
OL,15,Fexposure to pornography, to criminal
OL,16,Fgangs using online platforms to
OL,17,Frecruit children, the online world
OL,18,Fposes serious dangers.
