OL,3,CNext government should consider
OL,4,Cbanning phones for under-16s, report
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,F"Parents and schools face an uphill
OL,8,Fstruggle and Government must do more
OL,9,Fto help them meet this challenge. This
OL,10,Fmight require radical steps, such as
OL,11,Fpotentially a ban on smartphones for
OL,12,Funder-16s.
OL,14,F"Our report found that digital age of
OL,15,Fconsent checks are not fit for
OL,16,Fpurpose. We heard no evidence
OL,17,Fdemonstrating that 13-year-olds
OL,18,Funderstood the ramifications of
OL,19,Fsharing personal information online
OL,20,Fand today's report urges the
OL,21,FGovernment to increase this age to 16.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@AOU
